<subSubSection id="C37B652CB5014B11FF26FC7B591EFAF8" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDE36A7B5014B11FF26FC7B58FFFB9B" blockId="5.[132,776,1013,1390]" box="[132,207,1013,1039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36A7B5014B11FF26FB9B591EFAF8" blockId="5.[132,776,1013,1390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">
Populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D24B5014B11FE8BFB9B59CBFBB9" box="[297,507,1045,1071]" class="Liliopsida" family="Colchicaceae" genus="Merendera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FE8BFB9B59CBFBB9" box="[297,507,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Merendera montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 4 tepals, 4 stamens and 2 styles were found in south-eastern Andalusia and here described as the new variety 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D24B5014B11FE3AFBDB5A9EFBF9" authority="López-Tirado, 2022" authorityName="López-Tirado" authorityYear="2022" box="[408,686,1109,1135]" class="Liliopsida" family="Colchicaceae" genus="Merendera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="montana" status="var.nov." variety="paucitepala">
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FE3AFBDB5A23FBF8" box="[408,531,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">M.montana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FD9DFBDB5A9EFBF9" box="[575,686,1109,1135]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">paucitepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22657CEB5014B11FD16FBDB5B37FBF9" box="[692,775,1109,1135]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" rank="variety">var.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Morphometric parameters of the new 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D24B5014B11FDBBFBFA5AA7FB19" box="[537,663,1140,1167]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" rank="variety" variety="were">variety were</taxonomicName>
compared with the typical one (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF04B56B5014B11FECFFB1A59EEFB39" author="RICO E." box="[365,478,1172,1199]" editor="CASTROVIEJO S. &amp; AEDO C. &amp; LAINZ M. &amp; MUNOZ GARMENDIA F. &amp; NIETO FELINER G. &amp; PAIVA J. &amp; BENEDI C." firstAuthor="Rico" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" pagination="97 - 102" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/155647" refId="ref2077" refString="RICO E. 2013. - Merendera Ramond, in CASTROVIEJO S., AEDO C., LAINZ M., MUNOZ GARMENDIA F., NIETO FELINER G., PAIVA J. &amp; BENEDI C. (eds), Flora Iberica. Vol. 20. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 97 - 102. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 155647" title="Merendera Ramond" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Flora Iberica. Vol. 20" year="2013">Rico 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and no further differences were detected. Besides the 
<typeStatus id="54DA8805B5014B11FE01FB3B59E1FB59" box="[419,465,1205,1231]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality, it was observed near to 
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FF00FB5B597AFB78" box="[162,330,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Tranco del Perro</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FE20FB5A5A46FB79" box="[386,630,1236,1263]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">
Refugio 
<collectingCountry id="F3767637B5014B11FE77FB5A5A17FB78" box="[469,551,1236,1262]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Cañada</collectingCountry>
Rincón
</emphasis>
within 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D24B5014B11FD69FB5B59FEFA98" authority="de Cazorla, Segura y Las Villas" authorityName="de Cazorla, Segura y Las Villas" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scombridae" genus="Sierra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB5B5014B11FD69FB5B59FEFA98" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Sierra de Cazorla, Segura y Las Villas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Natural Park. It is expected that this 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D24B5014B11FF44FA9A5941FAB8" box="[230,369,1300,1326]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" rank="variety" variety="could">variety could</taxonomicName>
be more spread in Jaén province; surrounding provinces such as 
<collectingCountry id="F3767637B5014B11FE0EFABA5A38FAD8" box="[428,520,1332,1358]" name="Grenada" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Granada</collectingCountry>
and Albacete should be also prospected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
